regularTemplates.body:
Dear [MP_NAME],

I am writing to you with respect to the situation in Iran where the Islamic Republic government is committing crimes against humanity, has murdered upwards of 40,000 people in January, and is continuing its killings behind closed doors with or without illegal and summary trials. After weeks of complete internet shutdown, some Iranians in Iran now have intermittent access to the heavily-restricted internet and images and videos of the abhorrent crimes of the Islamic Republic regime have started to emerge. The regime will continue its killings, as it has in the last 47 years, unless the international community including the Government of Canada stands with the people of Iran and takes meaningful action to support the revolution for regime change. 
As a Member of the Parliament of Canada, a country that is home to one of the largest communities of the Iranian diaspora in the world, with highly educated immigrants that significantly contribute to Canada and its economy, the role of your office extends far beyond the Canadian borders. 

We ask that you:
- Speak up at the Parliament about the actions that Canada must take to put an end to the Islamic Republic’s crimes and hold the Government of Iran and its officials including those in Canada accountable;
- Support the revolution in Iran for regime change, engage with and support the opposition leader, Prince Reza Pahlavi and his efforts to transition Iran towards democracy; 
- Refrain from engaging and speaking with the lobbyists of the Islamic Republic - they are easy to identify: any group or person that advocates for reform in Iran instead of regime change is a lobbyist for the Islamic Republic and is complicit in its crimes;
- Establish a task force to identify those tied to the Islamic Republic who are currently residing and/or conduct business in Canada including current and former officials of the regime and their families, and take steps to freeze their assets and prohibit any dealings and transactions with them;
- Support the revolution in Iran for regime change, engage with and support the opposition leader Reza Pahlavi and his efforts towards a democratic transition after the collapse of the regime. 


We have reached a point where public announcements and condemnations are not sufficient. Meaningful action is required to put a stop to the Islamic Republic’s regime and its crimes. Lives are on the line and time is of the essence. Any delay in taking action directly translates to more loss of life. A revolution is underway and we need your support. 


[CONSTITUENCY_INFO]

Sincerely,

